datasets.name: 015fd821
datasets.query:
WITH pricing AS (
  SELECT
    p.pricing.effective_list.default AS price,
    p.price_start_time,
    p.sku_name,
    p.currency_code,
    case when p.sku_name LIKE ('%PRO%') then 'PRO' 
      WHEN p.sku_name LIKE ('%SERVERLESS%') THEN 'SERVERLESS'
      WHEN p.sku_name LIKE ('PREMIUM_SQL_COMPUTE') THEN 'CLASSIC'
    END AS warehouse_type,
    COALESCE(p.price_end_time, NOW()) AS price_end_time
  FROM
    system.billing.list_prices p
),
warehouse_creator as
(SELECT
  user_identity.email as warehouse_owner,
  GET_JSON_OBJECT(response.result, '$.id') AS warehouse_id
FROM
  system.access.audit
WHERE action_name in ('createWarehouse', 'createEndpoint')
and response.status_code = 200
),

usage_with_pricing AS (
  SELECT
    u.workspace_id,
    -- u.custom_tags,
    TRANSFORM(MAP_KEYS(custom_tags),(k, i) -> CONCAT(lower(k), '=', lower(MAP_VALUES(custom_tags) [i]))) AS key_value_tags,
    ifnull(u.usage_metadata.warehouse_id, u.sku_name) as warehouse_id,
    u.sku_name,
    p.warehouse_type,
    u.billing_origin_product,
    -- u.usage_start_time,
    p.price as price_per_unit,
    u.usage_date,
    sum(u.usage_quantity) as dbus,
    sum(u.usage_quantity) * p.price AS day_dollars
  FROM
    system.billing.usage u
    INNER JOIN pricing p ON p.sku_name = u.sku_name AND u.usage_start_time BETWEEN p.price_start_time AND p.price_end_time
  WHERE
    u.billing_origin_product = 'SQL'
    -- add warehouse_id check as some some records are serverless computes and jobs
    and u.usage_metadata.warehouse_id is not null
    AND u.usage_date BETWEEN :param_start_date AND :param_end_date
  group by all
),
ranked_usage AS (
  SELECT
    workspace_id,
    warehouse_id,
    key_value_tags,
    usage_date,
    warehouse_type,
    price_per_unit,
    sku_name,
    dbus, --  warehouse dbu units per day
    day_dollars, --  warehouse dollars per day
    sum(day_dollars) over (PARTITION BY warehouse_id) as warehouse_dollars, -- total warehouse spending over the period
    sum(day_dollars) over (PARTITION BY workspace_id) as workspace_dollars, -- total workspace spending over the period
    sum(day_dollars) over (PARTITION BY usage_date, workspace_id) as workspace_day_dollars,-- workspace dollars per day
    -- rank each warehouse cost per day
    dense_rank() OVER (PARTITION BY usage_date ORDER BY day_dollars DESC) AS warehouse_day_rank,
    -- rank each workspace cost per day
    dense_rank() OVER (PARTITION BY usage_date ORDER BY sum(day_dollars) over (PARTITION BY usage_date, workspace_id) DESC) AS workspace_day_rank,
    -- rank total warehouse cost over the period from param_start_date to param_end_date
    dense_rank() OVER (ORDER BY sum(day_dollars) over (PARTITION BY warehouse_id)  DESC NULLS LAST) AS warehouse_rank,
    -- rank total workspace cost over the period from param_start_date to param_end_date
    dense_rank() OVER (ORDER BY sum(day_dollars) over (PARTITION BY workspace_id)  DESC NULLS LAST) AS workspace_rank
  FROM
    usage_with_pricing
  WHERE 1=1
    AND (:workspace_id='All' OR workspace_id = :workspace_id)
    AND (:warehouse_id='All' OR warehouse_id = :warehouse_id)
    AND (:tags = 'All' or array_contains(key_value_tags, :tags))
)

SELECT
  CASE
    WHEN warehouse_rank <=:TopK THEN u.warehouse_id
    ELSE 'OTHER'
  END AS warehouse_topK,
  CASE
    WHEN workspace_rank <=:TopK THEN workspace_id
    ELSE 'OTHER'
  END AS workspace_topK,
  CASE
    WHEN warehouse_day_rank <=:TopK  THEN u.warehouse_id
    ELSE 'OTHER'
  END AS warehouse_day_topK,
  CASE
    WHEN workspace_day_rank <= :TopK THEN workspace_id
    ELSE 'OTHER'
  END AS workspace_day_topK,
  u.warehouse_id,
  workspace_id,
  u.key_value_tags,
  c.warehouse_owner,
  usage_date,
  warehouse_type,
  price_per_unit,
  sku_name,
  dbus,
  day_dollars
FROM
  ranked_usage u
  LEFT JOIN warehouse_creator c on c.warehouse_id = u.warehouse_id
GROUP BY all

datasets.name: c3d23285
datasets.query:
-- Statement allocated cost calculated logic is based off DBSQL Warehouse Advisor Observability Dashboard by  Databricks SQL SME group 
-- (https://github.com/CodyAustinDavis/dbsql_sme/tree/main/Observability%20Dashboards%20and%20DBA%20Resources/Observability%20Lakeview%20Dashboard%20Templates/DBSQL%20Warehouse%20Advisor%20With%20Data%20Model)
with pricing as (
    SELECT
    p.pricing.effective_list.default AS price,
    p.price_start_time,
    p.sku_name,
    p.currency_code,
    case when p.sku_name LIKE ('%PRO%') then 'PRO' 
      WHEN p.sku_name LIKE ('%SERVERLESS%') THEN 'SERVERLESS'
      WHEN p.sku_name LIKE ('PREMIUM_SQL_COMPUTE') THEN 'CLASSIC'
    END AS warehouse_type,
    COALESCE(p.price_end_time, NOW()) AS price_end_time
  FROM
    system.billing.list_prices p
),
raw_history as (
  SELECT
    workspace_id,
    statement_id,
    compute.warehouse_id AS warehouse_id,
    executed_by,
    statement_text,
    COALESCE(read_io_cache_percent, 0) AS read_io_cache_percent,
    from_result_cache,
    execution_status,
    ifnull(query_source.dashboard_id, query_source.legacy_dashboard_id) as dashboard_id,
    CASE WHEN query_source.job_info.job_id IS NOT NULL THEN 'JOB'
      WHEN query_source.legacy_dashboard_id IS NOT NULL THEN 'LEGACY DASHBOARD'
      WHEN query_source.dashboard_id IS NOT NULL THEN 'AI/BI DASHBOARD'
      WHEN query_source.alert_id IS NOT NULL THEN 'ALERT'
      WHEN query_source.notebook_id IS NOT NULL THEN 'NOTEBOOK'
      WHEN query_source.sql_query_id IS NOT NULL THEN 'SQL QUERY'
      WHEN query_source.genie_space_id IS NOT NULL THEN 'GENIE SPACE'
      ELSE 'ADHOC'
      END AS query_source_type,
    f.statement_type,
    COALESCE(client_application, 'Unknown') AS client_application,
    COALESCE(try_divide(total_duration_ms, 1000), 0) AS QueryRuntimeSeconds,
    COALESCE(try_divide(total_task_duration_ms, 1000), 0) AS CPUTotalExecutionTime,
    COALESCE(try_divide(execution_duration_ms, 1000), 0) AS ExecutionQueryTime,
    -- Included in Cost Per Query
    COALESCE(try_divide(compilation_duration_ms, 1000), 0) AS CompilationQueryTime,
    -- Included in Cost Per Query
    COALESCE(
      try_divide(waiting_at_capacity_duration_ms, 1000),
      0
    ) AS QueueQueryTime,
    COALESCE(
      try_divide(waiting_for_compute_duration_ms, 1000),
      0
    ) AS ComputeStartUpTime,
    COALESCE(try_divide(result_fetch_duration_ms, 1000), 0) AS ResultFetchTime,
    -- Metric for query cost allocation - 
    CASE
      WHEN COALESCE(try_divide(total_task_duration_ms, 1000), 0) = 0 THEN 0 -- exclude metadata operations
      ELSE COALESCE(try_divide(execution_duration_ms, 1000), 0) + COALESCE(try_divide(compilation_duration_ms, 1000), 0) -- Query total time is compile time + query execution time, excluding Queue & compute start up time
    END AS TotalResourceTimeUsedForAllocation,
    start_time,
    end_time,
    COALESCE(total_task_duration_ms / total_duration_ms, NULL) AS TotalCPUTime_To_Execution_Time_Ratio,
    --execution time does seem to vary across query type, using total time to standardize
    COALESCE(
      waiting_at_capacity_duration_ms / total_duration_ms,
      0
    ) AS ProportionQueueTime
  FROM
    system.query.history f
  WHERE
    1 = 1
    AND start_time BETWEEN :param_start_date :: timestamp
    AND :param_end_date :: timestamp -- TO DO: this technically does not line up with exact warehouse time window - need to split query time as well
    -- AND query_source.dashboard_id is not null
    AND statement_type IS NOT NULL
    AND (:workspace_id='All' OR workspace_id = :workspace_id)
    AND (:warehouse_id='All' OR compute.warehouse_id = :warehouse_id)
),

query_history_agg AS (
  SELECT
    *,
    SUM(TotalResourceTimeUsedForAllocation) OVER (partition by warehouse_id) AS TotalUsedTimeInWarehouse,
    -- Remove listing commands in time - this are essentially "free"
    SUM(COALESCE(TotalResourceTimeUsedForAllocation, 0)) OVER (PARTITION BY statement_text) AS TotalStatementTextTimeUsed,
    -- for query level aggregates
    try_divide(
      TotalResourceTimeUsedForAllocation,
      TotalUsedTimeInWarehouse
    ) AS ProportionOfWarehouseTimeUsedByQuery -- Remove listing commands in time - this are essentially "free"
  FROM
    raw_history
),
-- Warehouse Costs for the same query window
filtered_warehouse_usage AS (
  WITH trimmed_usage AS (
    SELECT
      usage_metadata.warehouse_id AS warehouse_id,
      p.warehouse_type,
      p.price as warehouse_unit_price,
      u.sku_name as sku_name,
      TRANSFORM(MAP_KEYS(custom_tags),(k, i) -> CONCAT(lower(k), '=', lower(MAP_VALUES(custom_tags) [i]))) AS key_value_tags,
      usage_start_time,
      usage_end_time,
      usage_quantity AS dbus,
      -- Start Time Range Trimming
      timestampdiff(SECOND, usage_start_time, :param_start_date) :: float AS seconds_before_start_range,
      timestampdiff(SECOND, usage_start_time, usage_end_time) :: float AS full_start_range_length,
      full_start_range_length - seconds_before_start_range AS seconds_remaining_in_original_start_range,
      greatest(:param_start_date, usage_start_time) AS trimmed_start_time,
      -- End Time Range Trimming
      least(:param_end_date, usage_end_time) AS trimmed_end_time,
      timestampdiff(SECOND, :param_end_date, usage_end_time) :: float AS seconds_after_end_range,
      timestampdiff(SECOND, usage_start_time, usage_end_time) :: float AS full_end_range_length,
      full_end_range_length - seconds_after_end_range AS seconds_remaining_in_original_end_range,
      -- Calculate trim proportion to multiple DBUs by proportion of the full hour in the active window
      try_divide(
        CASE
          WHEN seconds_before_start_range > 0 THEN (
            full_start_range_length - seconds_before_start_range
          )
          ELSE NULL
        END,
        full_start_range_length
      ) AS StartTrimProportion,
      try_divide(
        CASE
          WHEN seconds_after_end_range > 0 THEN (
            full_start_range_length - seconds_after_end_range
          )
          ELSE NULL
        END,
        full_start_range_length
      ) AS EndTrimProportion,
      COALESCE(
        COALESCE(EndTrimProportion, StartTrimProportion),
        1
      ) AS TrimProportion
    FROM
      system.billing.usage u
      inner join pricing p on p.sku_name = u.sku_name
      and u.usage_start_time between p.price_start_time
      and p.price_end_time
    WHERE
      1 = 1
      and usage_metadata.warehouse_id is not null
      AND usage_unit = 'DBU'
      AND (
        (
          usage_start_time BETWEEN :param_start_date :: timestamp
          AND :param_end_date :: timestamp
        )
        OR (
          usage_end_time BETWEEN :param_start_date :: timestamp
          AND :param_end_date :: timestamp
        )
      )
  )
  SELECT
    warehouse_id,
    warehouse_type,
    key_value_tags,
    SUM(dbus * TrimProportion) AS Total_Warehouse_Period_DBUs,
    SUM(dbus * TrimProportion * warehouse_unit_price) AS Total_Warehouse_Period_Dollars
  FROM
    trimmed_usage
  WHERE (:tags = 'All' or array_contains(key_value_tags, :tags))
  GROUP BY
    all
)
SELECT
  qh.workspace_id,
  qh.query_source_type,
  case when qh.dashboard_id is null then "OTHERS" else qh.dashboard_id end as dashboard_id,
  qh.executed_by,
  qh.statement_id,
  qh.warehouse_id,
  u.warehouse_type,
  u.key_value_tags,
  qh.statement_text,
  qh.QueryRuntimeSeconds,
  qh.CPUTotalExecutionTime,
  qh.ExecutionQueryTime,
  qh.CompilationQueryTime,
  qh.QueueQueryTime,
  qh.ComputeStartUpTime,
  qh.TotalResourceTimeUsedForAllocation,
  u.Total_Warehouse_Period_Dollars,
  qh.ProportionOfWarehouseTimeUsedByQuery,
  (u.Total_Warehouse_Period_Dollars :: float * ProportionOfWarehouseTimeUsedByQuery :: float) AS AllocatedQueryCostByTime
FROM
  query_history_agg AS qh
  LEFT JOIN filtered_warehouse_usage AS u ON u.warehouse_id = qh.warehouse_id
where
  1 = 1
  and (u.Total_Warehouse_Period_Dollars :: float * ProportionOfWarehouseTimeUsedByQuery :: float) > 0
order by (u.Total_Warehouse_Period_Dollars :: float * ProportionOfWarehouseTimeUsedByQuery :: float) desc

datasets.query:
select "All" as warehouse_id
union
(select distinct usage_metadata.warehouse_id from `system`.billing.usage
where usage_metadata.warehouse_id is not null
and usage_date BETWEEN :param_start_date AND :param_end_date);
